# Video

Use a video component to display YouTube videos in-product for customer use and convenience. It is recommended that embedded videos adhere to a 16:9 aspect ratio for best performance. The video player requires an `embed` url from YouTube in order to function properly; these urls are different than a standard YouTube URL. See the Embed URL section below for more details.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/video
```

```tsx
import { Video } from '@ids-ts/video';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `closeAriaLabel` | `string` | No | Label for screen readers for the close button |
| `minimizeAriaLabel` | `string` | No | Label for screen readers for the minimize button |
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | Whether or not the video is visible |
| `recFromCurrentChannelOnly` | `boolean` | No | Tells YouTube iframe to only show videos from the channel of the embedded video when paused or video ends |
| `restoreAriaLabel` | `string` | No | Label for screen readers for the restore button |
| `titleText` | `string` | No | Optional title string that overrides the YouTube |
| `url` | `string` | Yes | The YouTube embed URL of the video to play |
| `onCloseVideo` | `(event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLElement> \| React.KeyboardEvent) => void` | Yes | Called when the X icon is clicked to close the video. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface VideoProps extends ThemeableElement<'section'> {
  /** Label for screen readers for the close button */
  closeAriaLabel?: string;

  /** Label for screen readers for the minimize button */
  minimizeAriaLabel?: string;

  /** Whether or not the video is visible */
  open: boolean;

  /** Tells YouTube iframe to only show videos from the channel of the embedded video when paused or video ends */
  recFromCurrentChannelOnly?: boolean;

  /** Label for screen readers for the restore button */
  restoreAriaLabel?: string;

  /** Optional title string that overrides the YouTube */
  titleText?: string;

  /** The YouTube embed URL of the video to play */
  url: string;

  /** Callback function that fires when the X icon is clicked */
  onCloseVideo: (
    event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLElement> | React.KeyboardEvent<HTMLElement>
  ) => void;
}
```

</details>

